project_descr: Value Chains for Employment strengthened and livelihoods improved

outputs.output_descr: The aim of the Value Chains for Employment project is to improve livelihoods of the people of Bosnia and Herzegovina, and specifically in the Sarajevo  and Herzegovina  regions as well as the municipalities of Srebrenica, Milici and Bratunac, by producing new value or value added products, generating employment and incomes, and sustaining those currently in place.
